      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 326,
      "message": "For future reference, another way of dealing with \"too many 'continue' or 'break' statements\" is to extract the offending code block, sometimes the entire body of a loop, into a separate method.  That generally preserves the original form of the code, while satisfying sonar.  An IDE will do most of the work for you, though complaining about the \"continue\" and \"break\" statements, which you have to convert into appropriate \"return\" statements anyway.",
